00:56:53.470 --> 00:56:55.810
self-understanding about
political interest.

00:56:55.810 --> 00:56:58.350
One of the things we've been
learning in this century

00:56:58.350 --> 00:56:59.970
about our politics is
that people who care

00:56:59.970 --> 00:57:02.460
about what we think
of as kind of cultural

00:57:02.460 --> 00:57:05.360
and identity issues
much more than they care

00:57:05.360 --> 00:57:06.730
about economic issues.

00:57:06.730 --> 00:57:08.030
And in some ways both

00:57:08.030 --> 00:57:09.810
of the parties now are
advocating things that are

00:57:09.810 --> 00:57:14.510
against the economic interests
of their core constituents.

00:57:14.510 --> 00:57:17.460
And you know, republicans
are the party of the elderly

00:57:17.460 --> 00:57:19.050
that wants to change
social security,

00:57:19.050 --> 00:57:22.200
or they used to want to.

00:57:22.200 --> 00:57:24.300
They're the party of the
working class that wants

00:57:24.300 --> 00:57:25.690
to lower their boss' taxes.

00:57:25.690 --> 00:57:28.280
If you think about economics
that way, I mean politics

00:57:28.280 --> 00:57:30.550
that way as an extension
of economics,

00:57:30.550 --> 00:57:32.240
it just doesn't make sense.

00:57:32.240 --> 00:57:36.460
But the part coalition makes
more sense if you think

00:57:36.460 --> 00:57:37.760
about what it is that people

00:57:37.760 --> 00:57:40.500
in this economic
brackets value most

00:57:40.500 --> 00:57:42.910
and what they care about,
what they believe in.

00:57:42.910 --> 00:57:45.760
I think in that way, the
coalitions make some more sense.

00:57:45.760 --> 00:57:48.690
And so it may be that what
you're really seeing is

00:57:48.690 --> 00:57:51.320
that higher income people

00:57:51.320 --> 00:57:55.480
in America have certain
cultural attitudes and views

00:57:55.480 --> 00:57:59.570
that incline them more
toward the leftwing party

00:57:59.570 --> 00:58:01.820
and our politics, and
the working-class people

00:58:01.820 --> 00:58:05.310
in America tend to have more
conservative views on the issues

00:58:05.310 --> 00:58:06.610
that they care about most.

00:58:06.610 --> 00:58:09.470
So, you know, it used to be said
that conservatives care more

00:58:09.470 --> 00:58:12.270
about the culture and liberals
care most about the economy.

00:58:12.270 --> 00:58:14.540
But the right keeps
winning on the economy,

00:58:14.540 --> 00:58:15.840
and the left keeps
winning on the culture.

00:58:15.840 --> 00:58:18.480
So we're kind of
permanently frustrated.

00:58:18.480 --> 00:58:19.820
I think we're actually
at a point now

00:58:19.820 --> 00:58:22.090
where both coalitions
seem to care most

00:58:22.090 --> 00:58:25.010
about cultural issues
one way or another.

